    excerpt: "Empaths experience the world differently, absorbing the emotions and energy of those around them with an intensity that can be both illuminating and exhausting.",
    content: "Empaths experience the world differently, absorbing the emotions and energy of those around them with an intensity that can be both illuminating and exhausting. If you have ever walked into a room and immediately sensed the mood, or felt drained after spending time with certain people, you may carry empathic traits.\n\nBeing an empath is not a diagnosis. It exists on a spectrum, and most people fall somewhere between completely shielded and completely permeable. The challenge for those on the more sensitive end is learning to distinguish their own emotions from those they absorb from others.\n\nBoundary-setting is essential for empaths but often feels counterintuitive. It can seem selfish to protect your energy when you can literally feel someone else's pain. But an empath without boundaries is like a sponge that never gets wrung out. Eventually, you become so saturated with others' emotions that you lose touch with your own. Healthy boundaries allow you to use your gift without being consumed by it.",
