    content: "The average person consumes more information in a single day than someone in the 15th century encountered in their entire lifetime. This staggering volume of input has real consequences for mental clarity, emotional stability, and spiritual connection.\n\nDigital detox is not about rejecting technology. It is about establishing a conscious relationship with it. The constant stream of notifications, feeds, and updates fragments attention into ever-smaller pieces, making it nearly impossible to achieve the deep focus or quiet contemplation that personal growth requires.\n\nPractical digital detox does not require going off-grid. Start with intentional boundaries: no screens for the first hour after waking, designated phone-free zones in your home, one full day per week without social media. These small acts of reclamation add up, creating space for the kind of deep thinking and genuine connection that technology tends to crowd out.",
