    slug: "gematria-decoded",
    excerpt: "Gematria is an ancient practice of assigning numerical values to letters and words, revealing hidden connections and deeper meanings in text.",
    content: "Gematria is an ancient practice of assigning numerical values to letters and words, revealing hidden connections and deeper meanings in text. Originating in Hebrew tradition, gematria has been used for millennia to find layers of meaning in sacred texts and everyday language.\n\nIn Hebrew gematria, each letter has a fixed numerical value. Aleph equals 1, Bet equals 2, and so on, with some letters reaching into the hundreds. When two words share the same numerical value, practitioners consider them to be connected on a deeper level. This practice has been applied to the Torah, finding relationships between concepts that appear unrelated on the surface.\n\nPythagorean gematria applies similar principles to the English alphabet, mapping letters A through Z to numbers 1 through 9 in a repeating cycle. This accessible system allows anyone to explore the numerical vibrations of names, words, and phrases, adding another dimension to numerological practice.",
